n  Identity: ⚖️ Insurance Attorney (IDENTITY.md)\n  Workspace: ~/.openclaw/insurance_attorney_workspace\n  Agent dir: ~/.openclaw/agents/insurance-attorney/agent\n  Model: anthropic/claude-opus-4-6\n  Routing rules: 0\nRouting rules map channel/account/peer to an agent. Use --bindings for full rules.\nChannel status reflects local config/creds. For live health: openclaw channels status --probe.","cwd":"/Users/josearango/.openclaw/master_workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1773631904453}}
{"type":"message","id":"923b8207","parentId":"7468a295","timestamp":"2026-03-16T03:32:01.033Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Done! ⚖️ *Insurance Attorney is live!*\n\n*⚖️ INSURANCE ATTORNEY — HIRED & DEPLOYED*\n\n- **Name:** Insurance Attorney\n- **Specialty:** Senior Policyholder Insurance Litigation\n- **Side:** *ALWAYS the policyholder. NEVER the carrier.*\n- **Status:** ✅ Active\n\n*What it fights for:*\n\n*🏠 Property Claims*\n- Hurricane, wind, water, fire, theft damage\n- Homeowners (HO-3, HO-6) & commercial policies\n- Claim filing strategy & documentation\n- Proof of loss preparation\n- Replacement cost vs. actual cash value disputes\n- Flood insurance (NFIP) appeals\n- Wind vs. water causation fights\n\n*🔥 Bad Faith Litigation*\n- Civil Remedy Notice (CRN) filing under FL §624.155\n- Lowball offers & unreasonable delays\n- Failure to investigate or communicate\n- Biased engineers & cherry-picked evidence\n- Punitive damages & consequential damages\n\n*❌ Claim Denials*\n- \"Pre-existing damage\" — counter strategies\n- \"Wear and tear\" — rebuttal arguments\n- \"Late notice\" — prejudice analysis\n- \"Policy exclusions\" — narrow construction\n- Examination Under Oath (EUO) prep\n- Appraisal process strategy\n\n*💼 Commercial Claims*\n- Business interruption / income loss\n- Builder's risk disputes\n- CGL coverage fights\n- D&O and E&O claims\n\n*🚗 Auto Insurance*\n- PIP disputes\n- UM/UIM claims & stacking\n- Total loss valuation challenges\n- Diminished value claims\n\n*⚠️ Post-2022 Florida Reform Expert*\n- Knows exactly how SB 2-A and SB 7052 changed the game\n- Strategies that still work under new rules\n- 2-year statute of limitations awareness\n- One-way fee elimination workarounds\n\n*Example tasks:*\n- \"My insurance denied my hurricane claim — what are my options?\"\n- \"Citizens offered me $12K on a $95K claim — how do I fight this?\"\n- \"Review this denial letter and tell me if I have a case\"\n- \"What's the bad faith process in Florida step by step?\"\n- \"My adjuster is lowballing me — what's the strategy?\"\n- \"Is it worth hiring a public adjuster or going straight to an attorney?\"\n\n⚠️ *Research-level analysis only, not licensed legal advice.*\n\n---\n\n*👑 YOUR FULL TEAM:*\n- 👑 Master Agent — orchestrator & research\n- 🔍 SEO Agent — search engine optimization\n- 🏠 Real Estate Agent — property & investment strategy\n- 🏛️ Land Use Attorney — zoning & land use law\n- 🌿 Environmental Engineer — environmental compliance\n- 📊 McKinsey Consultant — business strategy & viability\n- 🏦 Investment Banker — deals, valuations & capital markets\n- ⚖️ Insurance Attorney — policyholder litigation & bad faith\n\nYou're building a war room, Jose. Who's next? 🚀"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"anthropic","model":"claude-opus-4-6","usage":{"input":1,"output":755,"cacheRead":65401,"cacheWrite":754,"totalTokens":66911,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773631904454}}
